# user-select and Safari

When setting `user-select`, always declare the WebKit-prefixed property **immediately before** the standard property so Safari and Safari on iOS are covered and linters stay quiet.

```scss
// ❌ BAD — triggers Safari compatibility warnings
.panel {
  user-select: none;
}

// ✅ GOOD
.panel {
  -webkit-user-select: none;
  user-select: none;
}
```

Apply the same pattern for every value (`none`, `text`, `all`, `auto`, etc.). Do not use only `-webkit-user-select` without the unprefixed `user-select`.
